title: Excel Palace Hotel
address: 25(D-1), New University Ave Road, Bahan Tsp., Northern Yangon, Yangon 11181
descriptions: Warmly decorated rooms with Wi-Fi in an unpretentious hotel offering a restaurant & breakfast.
complete_address: {"borough":"","street":"25(D-1), New University Ave Road, Bahan Tsp., Northern Yangon","city":"Yangon","postal_code":"11181","state":"","country":"MM"}
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Nick N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The desk staff was awesome!!  They were very helpful and spoke a good bit of English.  The upscale home turned hotel, looked tired and in need of repair.  But there was a lot of very nice woodwork all around and the hotel had \"character,\" for sure! ||||I personally enjoyed sitting out by a small balcony reading and watching the birds.  ||||They had a free breakfast in another next door restaurant which four breakfast options.  The breakfast was very good, and the waiters/waitresses were very friendly and helpful.  We had three of the four breakfast options and they were all good.||||Here was one of the meals:   Steamed Dimsum, fried noodles, chicken sausage,  sliced Honey Dew and Papaya with something on it that tastes like a perfume smells but is really good with coffee and Oolong tea.  Oh,  and some  kind of  a fish meat based hot sauce...also good.||||From the airport to the hotel we got a taxi from the taxi desk inside for 6,000 MMK but going back we found a taxi that only charged us 4,000 MMK.||||It was a nice place to stay on a budget!!  I would stay there again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ukairo_dash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcnOWm00_8Vg0_qD09-e04s-i2bb5F6bVsdwxSboR_yrT1yPvciwzMvgtJ8p5a3bvmZzg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Stayed at the Excel Palace for 4 nights of a month long stay in Yangon. So in an apples-to-apples comparison, it is close to 3 stars. . .  but falls short in several ways. You be the judge:||The room was large and wasnt lacking for furniture, but the drapes were badly torn and the bedding had a lot of visible stains.  ||The plush headboard was likewise filthy and the pillows were very well used.||Moving on to the bathroom, the shower had plenty of hot water but 75% flowed out if the downspout, leaving the shower with rather weak pressure. The shower head was mounted below chest level. I brought these issues up with the staff on day 1, but there was no change during our time there.||Finally, the free breakfast. It was next door in a busy restaurant. There is a choice of 4 set menus with no changes allowed (it is not a buffet). Most hotels (every one we have stayed at in Yangon) have a buffet. The restaurant wouldn't even give us water, only tea or coffee (which I doubt is from filtered water). The water at the hotel is turbid (a light brown color), and I imagine that is what you get with the tea/coffee.||We brought our own bottled every morning which was not a problem.||I would give details about the number of flies in the restaurant, but suffice it to say that if you dont like flies buzzing everywhere, you might want to avoid the place.||The location (walking distance to the lake) was ok. A longer walk to other restaurants (with the exception of a Thai restaurant just across the street which was excellent).||All in all, I'd like to give it 3 stars. The house is nice. They could quickly fix most issues. But it seems the management is not of a mind to follow through.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"John C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Hotels in Yangon, now that Myanmar is the \"flavour of the month\", are now very expensive with the xception of the Excel Palace. It is not downtown but close to Inya Lake and the Inya Lake Hotel which is where I wanted to be close to.||It is an old private home and has no lift but spiral staircases, so be warned.||My room was large with two twin beds. All shampoos, soap etc were all supplied, as was free water every day. There is a safe in the room. The WiFi worked well.||There is also a well stocked bar fridge and the beer price was cheaper than buying outside!||The reception staff could not be more helpful...nothing was too much trouble.||The included breakfast is not in the Hotel but just around the corner in a restaurant.||The service there was a mixture of very good, when the waitresses were working our table but a bit hit and miss when it was waiters!!||Taxis are everywhere and very cheap so it is easy to get to anywhere you want to go with no problems.||Would I stay there again...you bet I would...very happily.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We only arrived at 4pm and left at 5am the following morning but the service and assistance we received from the front desk was outstanding. We needed a bus booked the following morning and that was no problem – they also had the taxi ready for us at 5am the following morning before we even got down to reception. The room itself was so big (but a refreshing change from some others), that it had two air conditioners. We were on the top floor – if you have an irrational fear of pigeons, maybe request a room on a lower floor, as we had a few scratching around on the roof, not enough to wake us up though.||||We didn’t get to try breakfast before we left. There are a few decent looking restaurants right near the hotel although we didn’t get a chance to try them either. The Excel Palace is in walking distance to Inya Lake and only a short drive to Shwedagon. Unless you want to be in walking distance of Sule Paya and Bogyoke Markets, I’d recommend this place purely for the service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kayk44","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdGDJ6WBs5CBoNVcQAwShh25kntoFa0rN3szxhkmmJHnXagNPuSfO1BRpzbnKc5wyCe_g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at Excel Palace Hotel for 22 days.  First and foremost, we mention our #1 staff.  Simon, the manager, and also the assistant manager who went out of their way to assist us.  From city directions, room comfort, even impromptu language lessons, they were there with a smile.  Our room was comfortable, clean and quiet.  The location of the hotel, just off New University Avenue, allowed for peaceful nights, no traffic noise at all.  There are good restaurants nearby and downtown is just a short taxi ride away.  We will certainly return to Excel Palace when returning to Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"neamman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeiIm6t64oXJwlfKKV-SU2ENLb40SwZCvBWRts5o7WimonLggB5R8bs4qOdTbCTDXjyRQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"An old converted house which provided what I expected for the price paid. Staff very friendly and helpful, location reasonable for the price..facilities old and somewhat dated but no problems. A bit of a walk in humid Yangon to the restaurant which serves as the hotel facility but food was not bad and the staff good. Dont expect 5 star facilities but be happy with the average services provided but provided with a big smile and helpful attitude. No problems","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"James G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The decor is old and tired, but it is clean as much as it can be considering its age. Good location near Myanmar Plaza.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dave P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at Yankin on our first night in Myanmar - after a long travel (2 days from UK via HK) we were late getting in. Reception was dealt with quickly, and although the restaurant was closed, they found some beers for us, and allowed us to use the facilities to eat food which we obtained from nearby. Rooms were good, clean and well equipped. Breakfast was great, with omelettes cooked to order as well as the usual buffet fare. We travelled rounf Myanmar and returned to this hotel 2 weeks later to the same standard of service. Can't comment on the nearby ameneties, or the area in general as we were merely 'passing through' and needed a bed for the night. Overall, a good hotel with everything you need for a short stay. Probably not best location if you want a week here, but for us it was ideal. (We stayed in March, but Trip Advisor is playing up and keeps defaulting to todays date!)","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Hotel Shwe Eain Taw
address: E Horse Race Course Rd, Yangon 11181
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Theo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1q9-gRFTa-cXzjc58mcRbRj__l9RydXLgOSW0ZmxRcQ0xXuRm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is my new favorite hotel. The prices here at the time I got here was a bargain!

You get to have free breakfast and a very large room for under $15.

Not too bad...

The only downside is the location. It is terribly far from anywhere I deem fun and exciting. It is 50 minutes away walking distance to the park. 45 minutes away from a decent gym. The market is also 20 minutes of walking.

If you are a solo traveller who loves to walk and loves affordable stays that punches above it's weight. Stay here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0YIweIXQ2WTpaUERafUUsjhqZ0YKEz5uIycz0&fid=0x0:0x1b5bc3fb87e20b49"],"When":"2024-1-14"},{"Name":"Steve R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I booked the hotel for 3 of us in a family room for 3 nights. We were running the Yangon marathon (superb) and it is 2k from the start we walked home its that close.  ||||The hotel dosnt look great with ageing decor and a tired looking exterior. Thats where the negatives stop. ||||Firstly lets put this in perspctive,our room cost 63 usd (20 bucks each) including a very nice breakfast. ||||On arrival we were greeted with an orange juice and taken to our room by 3 porters lugging our bags up 4 stories to our room. We had a fantastic view (see picture), flat screen tv with sports and movies in english, newly installed air con, en suite with electric shower (reliably warm) and comfortable beds with clean sheets and towels. What else do you want. ||||The staff are so helpful bringing up water, beers, food and anything else we needed no matter what time of the day. The breakfast is great and they even remember if you like ketchip or chilli sauce and your choice of fruit the next day. The eggs are perfect!||||On the last night I sat and watched football with the local guys on a 40" TV and we had a great laugh whilst I ate my excellent 3 dollar special fried rice packed with chicken, pork, prawns...that I had no chance of finishing due to the volume.||||All in all a fantastic place which is 15 mins from airport and anything else in the city.  With taxis costing about 3 dollars to just about anywhere.  ||||This is not the ritz but is clean, authentic with great people. I would stay here again and again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Canndy H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The location is away from the city but transportation is not the problem as Yangon city is a TAXI city. Anyway to cut the talk short, watch what you eat and don't be a fool.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dinesh kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_GuDRTv1WgjN1nG59cJbQ5XBwhgOcvyBTy3ErbwqA6oUWZWG3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"New review 2019:

The hotel has been upgraded with the same excellent service as before. The rooms are clean and maintained well. They even have an ATM in the lobby. There is a 24hour CityMart (local supermarket) nearby. Since the hotel is on the main road, you can easily get Grab (like Uber car sharing service) and go around the city.

Do read my previous review below:

*****************************
Old review from 2017 below:

We stayed in the hotel for 3 nights in the Superior twin room and 2 nights in the Junior Suite B with Bathtub. As most of the reviews have already mentioned,  choose the rooms towards the back of the hotel (away from the road) and preferably to the right (facing east), these rooms have a better view and also you will get a glimpse of the rising sun. The hotel's buffet breakfast is great and each day they have a special local cuisine. This, in my opinion, would be a very safe way to try out the local dishes. The staff can speak English and are very friendly. The rooms are clean and we'll  maintained. The only problem is  that the doors do not appear to be sound proof and could be a problem if there are a lot of guests moving in-and-out of their rooms. TIP: There is a City Mart outlet straight down the road, about 15mins walk. There is a hospital nearby. There are some great food places in about 15mins walk.  (Note: photos are from the Junior Suite B room #403)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTRys335Gz8GYnI6YYBqGeugAo2Gk_wDNJK7Uv&fid=0x0:0x2c8d2472717556e6"],"When":"2018-1-7"},{"Name":"Sandy’s Shine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXd9XwYaXMx0VXxehGbmy_BXGG7o4D1R7qOLglJAXom2nLJ9IM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best technology in the leather industry","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ian Borja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNLX_Fs9Bq4tJkkoiCk_V6a2wYuYVowqo_cuP2tYcQNCXRug1DBw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small hotel of about 20 rooms. They do have good bed sheets, nice cozy room, very clean toilet and bathroom, and their towels are nice too.

They also have a simple buffet breakfast but would surely be filling. They have the normal fried rice, noodles, veggies, fishball, mominga, congee, bread, coffee & tea, different spreads, cereal, juice and fruits.

All staff, including the owner James, are very friendly  and they will make sure you will have the best stay.

Downside is location is in a main highway, but the noise is bearable. It is located a bit far from downtown area. Cab fare though is very inexpensive in Myanmar especially if you use Grab. If you let the front desk of the hotel book your Grab ride, you will even get a.discount.

Definitely this is a value for money hotel.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"陳適恆","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9Qa9YgyEIj_SG6Dkjal_b0smqbVY9X9C36qkb8MzTlsHDqg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is one of the best hotel I have ever stay in my life. title: Asian Smile Hotel
address: No. 324, Thanthumar Road, Thuwanna, Yangon 11072
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Brandon Rudd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL3BEm67ErtBvBTnTEY_JdnDPNZmcEPQkFQ8FQpZRsN2KeORA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An amazing place to stay if you really want to get lost in Myanmar! The staff are super kind and helpful, alongside being quite amusing at times.

They may not speak much English but they more than make up for it with service, not to mention they are very generous. A person here let me borrow some flip flops for the time I went to pagoda and helped me dress in their traditional outfit. Thanks to them I have a great experience in the country.

The location is pretty convenient too if you use the grab app, you can book a taxi and take a ride to downtown in about 10 minutes.

The room also has all the basic necessities and even come with free body wash and shampoo incase you run out as well as toothbrush.

The power may go out a few times but thats not their fault, its the countries power grid with rolling blackouts and they try to keep the power going with a generator I believe. The hot water in the shower is a little short but with how hot the country is it didn't bother me.

Hopefully they see this so thank you Asian Smile Hotel!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Myo Myint oo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOmactE_SsuEBl2unndIH-zfOLgexF7ZWcsQAWzZo2mqLLULTKcA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Wide and clean room. From the moment I stepped into the lobby, I was captivated by the modern and elegant design. The architecture is stunning, and it sets the tone for a luxurious experience.

The rooms are incredibly spacious and well-appointed. The attention to detail is evident, from the comfortable bedding. I felt like every possible need was anticipated and met, making my stay exceptionally comfortable.

What truly sets the Grand Galaxy Hotel apart is the outstanding service. The staff members are not only professional but also warm and welcoming. They go out of their way to ensure that guests feel attended to and valued. Whether it was a request for room service or assistance with local recommendations, the staff was always ready to help with a smile.

Dining at the hotel was a highlight of my stay. The variety of culinary options catered to every taste, and the quality of the food was outstanding. The chefs clearly prioritize using fresh and high-quality ingredients, creating a memorable dining experience.

The hotel's amenities are top-notch with a well-equipped fitness center.

The Grand Galaxy Hotel's location is also worth mentioning. It's conveniently situated, allowing easy access to key attractions and making it a great base for both business and leisure travelers.
Overall, my experience at the Grand Galaxy Hotel was exceptional. I would highly recommend it to anyone looking for a blend of luxury, comfort, and outstanding service. It truly made my trip memorable, and I look forward to returning in the future😆","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Road710189","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The room with a street view looks grand. Late check out is not allowed even for 3pm though my check in was 9pm.
And our family stayed there 4 nights.
No favour was shown upon my request.
Breakfast was not up to standard like 2019.
I will look into another hotel next time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Htike Aung Kyaw (ထိုက်အောင်ကျော်)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPg11AiMc4bQilh5xSPvnX1bN9Xrh58DFsOWdiTAB6ECrWVZuLrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Seems overrated. We checked-in around 3PM. Says you can check-in starting at 2PM. But when we arrived, the room wasn't quite ready yet. They were still fixing the water heater. They informed us that we'll be able to use hot water by night-time. The Side Table and Stools weren't even arranged properly when we arrived. We specifically requested the lake view room but was allocated at the 5th floor where the lake can't be seen as it's covered by trees. Still we get the view of Shwedagon Pagoda though. The room was hot, humid and a bit dusty when we checked in. Bed sheets are stained in some places but we didn't complain. What I was disgusted most by is the mold in Shower Curtains. Yuck! And hair remains in the bathtub and floor near the bed. At night, I turned on hot water and all I got was air, rusted brown water and cold water. I called them to check and they came in claiming the water is usable and is warm. It wasn't. Don't let me start with the room key card... Works 1 out of 30 tries. They came to change batteries both in the evening and the next morning. Every time we get out of the room we get locked out even though we have the key card with us. The only good thing was the tasty breakfast with a wide variety to choose from. Even for breakfast, the dining room arrangement sucked. They put two extra tables and chairs close to the buffet table and we have to tuck through these to get the food. Ugh... And they rang the doorbell at 7 AM mistakenly with the next room who were to check-out that morning. Didn't even say they were sorry for the interruption. We were given breakfast tickets but when we arrived at the dining room, no one was there to collect it so we left these tickets on the table after we were done eating. Guess what? They called us at 9AM and said it was the last call for breakfast. Good that they remind us for Breakfast, bad that they suck at who has finished eating and who have not. Overall, it seems overrated and overpriced compared to other hotels in town. Maybe they treat us locals differently from foreigners, not sure about that, as the room rates for locals and foreigners are different. But I think, for the same price, there are many hotels out there that give better service and facilities than those provided here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTjv-D6zKesrZz3a9TCruPYLhsrV5_JvBM9upK&fid=0x0:0xf4763ad7a8ba89c5"],"When":"2023-6-3"}]
